premise_source_doc_sentence: Commercially sold borax is partially dehydrated .
The property was sold to the Death Valley Hotel Company in 1956 , and finally to the National Park Service .

Borax first came into common use in the late 19th century when Francis Marion Smith 's Pacific Coast Borax Company began to market and popularize a large variety of applications under the 20 Mule Team Borax trademark , named for the method by which borax was originally hauled out of the California and Nevada deserts in large enough quantities to make it cheap and commonly available .
In 1899 , `` Borax '' Smith , founder of Pacific Coast Borax Company joined forces with Baker to form Borax Consolidated , Ltd. .

The incorporation included the Sterling Borax Company and the Suckow Property which is now operated as the Rio Tinto Borax Mine , the largest open pit mine in California and the largest borax mine in the world where almost half of the world 's borates are now produced .
